This guide outlines our best practices for writing software, currently focusing on Python (backend) and TypeScript (frontend).

over Cleverness:** Code should be easy to read and understand. - **Consistency:** Stick to our conventions, even if you have personal preferences. - **Documentation:** Good code is well-documented. Leave meaningful comments and docstrings.
